Close curly brace and the next "else", "catch" and "finally" keywords should be on two different lines
Why is this an issue? Shared coding conventions make it possible for a team to collaborate efficiently. This rule makes it mandatory to place a closing curly brace and the next else, catch or finally keyword on two different lines. 
### Noncompliant
public void myMethod() {
  if(something) {
    executeTask();
  } else if (somethingElse) {          // Noncompliant
    doSomethingElse();
  }
  else {                               
     generateError();
  }

  try {
    generateOrder();
  } catch (Exception e) {
    log(e);
  }
  finally {
    closeConnection();
  }
}
 
### Compliant
public void myMethod() {
  if(something) {
    executeTask();
  }
  else if (somethingElse) {
    doSomethingElse();
  }
  else {
     generateError();
  }

  try {
    generateOrder();
  }
  catch (Exception e) {
    log(e);
  }
  finally {
    closeConnection();
  }
}
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
### Compliant
